<section class="home-primary">

	<div class="landing-content-container">

		<h3>Why do artists need ArtYam?</h3>

		<p>Artists need ArtYam because it overcomes the 3 biggest obstacles to selling more art in non-gallery venues:</p>

		<br>

		<ol class="landing-page-list">
			
			<li><span class="red-text">Challenge #1:</span> Venue staff often lack the incentive and/or knowledge to sell art</li>

			<p>For most non-gallery venues, selling art is not their primary business; therefore, the venue staff have very little incentive to sell an artist's work or even know anything about it.  This means many missed opportunities to convert a potential buyer from "interested" to "buying" because they cannot get more information about the artist or their work.</p>

			<p><span class="green-text paragraph-intro">Solution:</span> ArtYam creates online tear sheets that provide potential buyers with instant access to additional information about artists and their work. These tear sheets provide information that simply cannot fit on printed placards below a display.</p>

			<br>

			<li><span class="red-text">Challenge #2:</span> It's difficult to engage potential buyers after they leave the venue</li>

			<p>Traditional advice on engaging collectors after they leave a venue where an artist's work is displayed is to provide something for the collector to take with them, such as a business card or printed promotional material.  However, these printed materials  have limited effectiveness because they have a tendency to get misplaced, either by the venue or the potential buyer.</p>

			<p><span class="green-text paragraph-intro">Solution:</span> ArtYam gives art collectors the ability to email to themselves a detailed tear sheet for an artist's work in order to review later. Additionally, ArtYam sends follow-up emails to determine if a collector is still interested in buying the piece.</p>

			<br>

			<li><span class="red-text">Challenge #3:</span> No instant purchasing options</li>

			<p>Artists frequently lose sales between the time an art collector contacts them through traditional channels (like email) and when the artist redirects them to a third party payment processor, like Paypal or SquareUp. Collectors may lose interest or simply forget to complete the transaction.</p>  

			<p><span class="green-text paragraph-intro">Solution:</span> ArtYam gives collectors the option to buy an artist's work on-the-spot with any major credit card through the artwork's easily accessible online tear sheet.</p>

		</ol>

	</div>

</section>


